    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-05-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-05-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="662"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d662">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 3742/7.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President-elect <persName type="from">Leguia</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima, Peru</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-05-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 29, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I deeply appreciate Mrs. Root’s and your congratulations upon my presidential
                    election and tender you my sincerest thanks therefor.</p>
                <p>I regard your kind message as a further proof of friendship toward Peru, which my
                    administration will at all times reciprocate.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Leguia.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
